{
  "stem": "10588.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And he-- not even to his father would he complain.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And one time-- I'm just going to make it brief because it's-- the-- in the coldest winter night, in a drunken stupor, his father threw him out in the cold night, dragged him by the head, and threw him out.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "[BACKGROUND NOISE] And he was-- and he was-- he got himself up, and he went off wherever his eyes took him.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And he was traveling, and then he came in in a big city.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And when he came in there, he was looking for a job, and he became a porter, and again, was abused constantly.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Again, he was silent.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Then-- I'm going, like, quickly through it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Then a woman who had a child that was not his child, an infant, that he married.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And he took the infant when she ran off.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "She left him alone.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And when the infant became 15 years old, he threw out his-- the man who raised him and abused him again.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And on and on, till finally one day, he was run over by a horse and carriage.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And he, whatever happened, he never complained, never raised his voice-- not to God, not to man.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "His suffering was more terrible than Job's, but never complained.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "That's-- and then finally, even in the hospital, when he lie in the hospital, he, where everybody is allowed to scream and he wasn't treated well because had not enough money to pay.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And in silence, he lived.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "In silence, he died.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And when they buried him, and they put the piece of wood, a woman, the gravedigger's wife, the wind blew away the piece of wood.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And nobody knew where he was, who was laying where.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "That this was Bontsha.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
